Gunmen attacked a driver attached to the Supreme Court’s Justice Njoki Ndung’u on Friday evening and made away with her official car.
Identified as Stephen Thuku, the justice’s driver was reportedly blocked by another car at Nairobi’s Githurai Mwihoko area. Three men with guns stormed into the vehicle he was driving and took control of it.



